Of course, that assumes that the reactor never goes boom, or that criminal elements in the design and construction of one's fancy new reactor don't have your state spend 12 billion dollars for not one Wattsworth of electricity generated. <a href="https://thebulletin.org/2021/08/us-attorney-details-illegal-acts-at-construction-projects-sealing-the-fate-of-the-nuclear-renaissance/" title="thebulletin.org">https://thebull<span class="substr"> </span></a> [thebulletin.org]</p></div>
