	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64466783">One of the problems with nuclear reactors is that large scale ones have more significant heat disipation problems. This is why they have to be located near highly reliable water sources like major rivers, lakes and oceans. It's your size argument in reverse: smaller reactors will avoid some problems that larger reactors have. Now, whether that is enough to offset the increase in costs you outline I do not know but I do not think it is quite as obvious as you think, especially when you factor in environmenta</div>
	</div>

