	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64466673"><p>That being the driver makes complete sense. Before I scrolled down to this post I was contemplating what problem these reactors solve.</p><p>The only problem miniature reactors solve is "doing something, anything, to say we're deploying nukes, while remaining within a fixed (insufficient) budget".</p><p>In political terms,"fixed budget" means "we don't dare raise more revenue."</p><p>In modern western politics, "we don't dare raise more revenue" means "we don't dare tax the rich."</p></div>
