		 	<span id="comment_score_64466809" class="score"> (<a href="#" onclick="getModalPrefs('modcommentlog', 'Moderation Comment Log', 64466809); return false"><span class=opt>Score:</span>3</a>, Informative)</span></h4>
		</div>
		<div class="details">
			<span class="by"><span class="byby">by </span><a href="//slashdot.org/~XXongo">XXongo</a>  <span class="uid"><a href="//slashdot.org/~XXongo">( 3986865 )</a></span></a></span><span class="writes" style="display:none"> writes:</span> 
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_64466809"></span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64466809"><p><div class="quote"><p>You should be thanking the communists for bringing the cost of solar down to pennies on the dollar.</p></div><p>Not sure what you refer to as "communists". The cost of solar was brought down by a focused research program through the 80s and 90s, funded in the US by the Department of Energy (but also with significant work in Europe and some brilliant work at University of New South Wales in Australia). Is that "communist"? It is the hybrid economy that we have in the US.</p><p><div class="quote"><p>It certainly wasn't capitalists that had any interest in that.</p></div><p>But, turns out it was. China has capitalists, and they grabbed on to solar production in order to make money.</p></div>
	</div>

